  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Social Work Associate",
  "description": "<p>SANA strives to educate the community on the harms of drug abuse, provide support for persons-in-recovery towards desistance, and advocate for a drug-free society. SANA’s Aftercare Department provides case management services for ex-drug offenders and their families in the community. We support their long-term recovery and reintegration through specialised case management support and also partner with other agencies to coordinate holistic support for our clients.<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong>:</p><p>1. <strong>Intake Briefing and Client Screening</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct intake briefings at CNB sections of police stations (either Bedok or Woodlands) to potential clients to seek informed consent before they opt in to receive SANA services.</li></ul><ul><li>The briefings will take place multiple times a week (2 to 4 days including 1 weekday night per week)</li></ul><ul><li>Collect basic information from clients that opt in to receive SANA services.</li></ul><p>2.<strong> Clinical Work</strong> </p><ul><li>Conduct intake assessments, case planning and intervention for cases.</li></ul><p>3. <strong>Operations </strong></p><ul><li>Work independently and in a team to meet operational functions at CNB sections of police stations. Be diligent in completing administrative tasks.</li></ul><p>4. <strong>Other Duties</strong></p><ul><li>To work on ad-hoc projects, and events, when required.</li></ul><ul><li>To carry out any other duties assigned by Management.</li></ul><p><strong>Technical Competencies:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in Counselling, Psychology, Social Work, or Sociology</li></ul><ul><li>Ability to relate with ex-offenders and their families.</li></ul><p><strong>Core Competencies:</strong></p><p>1. Good team player and pleasant disposition.</p><p>2. Strong conceptual, and organizational abilities.</p><p>3. Good interpersonal, communication, and writing skills.</p><p>4. Mature, independent and positive work attitude.<br /><br /><strong>Preferred achievements / characteristics:</strong></p><p>1. Good understanding of the principles of drug addiction and recovery</p><p>2. Preferably able to communicate with Mandarin- or Malay-speaking clients</p><p>3. Candidates with experience working with ex-offenders would be an added advantage</p>",
